text: The angiana tree frog (Litoria angiana) is a large tree frog from Papua New Guinea and Indonesia. Male adult frogs are 50 to 55 mm long from nose to rear end and females can be 80 mm long. They can be brown or green with a dark stripe on the sides. There are yellow spots around the stripe. They live near rivers and in forests. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Angiana tree frog
